    • DPM++ Series(SDE Karras, 2M Karras, etc.)

    • kl-f8-anime2.vae

    • CLIP skip = 1

LoRA training info

  • trained on sd-scripts by kohya_ss. Thank you a lot!

  • based on Animefull-pruned

    • 4x low quality 41 images

    • 8x medium quality 32 images

    • 16x high quality 45 images

  • replaced character feature tags with gold city \(umamusume\)

    • horse girl, horse tail, blonde hair, blue eyes, etc.

  • resolution : 768x768

  • rank=alpha=16

  • batch size = 4, 4 epochs trained

  • other settings included in training_data.zip

All uploaded images are generated by AOM3A1

items.name: KitchenSinkVer1.8
items.description:
KitchenSink V1.8 + 1.8L
A SD 2.1 768+ Boosted Artistic General Model

[[ this version is now archived and will not change. Mar 16th 2023 ]]
[[ PLEAE USE VERSION 2 IN MY PROFILE. SFW/NSFW ]]


Added LORA blend. GALLERY for GRIDS!! (Attachment limits sorry! Also civitai renames things I don't know why, on my pc it's named KitchenSinkVer1.8L etc. I suggest renaming to keep nice and clean after downloading)

[ This model is a merge of all 2.1 based ~ 768+ models because I got sick of swapping between models and 512px is too low really. ]

  • What the model differences are:

    1.8 = (the sloppy fun drunk) broad artistic vivid. Not scared to spill the wine while tipsy painting. Oh I made a Salvator Mundi? Cool.

    Example: The flower rose prompts. Vivid & vibrant.

    1.8L ( for Lora blended in) = Less drunk with a sharpened crayon. Dinosaurs? ya gotchya, I won't make them as gross (Thanks dino lora's!) BUT it is much less vivid and punchy vibrant.

  • Base 2.1 !!! > Don't forget the included YAML! (place in same folder as model. rename to same exact name as model! IE: KitchenSinkVer1.8 )

    [FYI You still need a yaml for 2.1 stuff - I don't know why some people say you don't anymore. For those reading it's less the auto11 not needing it and more that it is starting to give errors when merging/pruning/etc if you do not include your custom YAML file.
    -> On this model please use my included sink yaml merci!]

  • Resolutions 768+ (768x768, 768x1024, 1024x768 ++ etc)

  • No clip nonsense, no vae nonsense, bog standard SD setup, simple to complex prompting as you wish, negatives not really required (fyi: the more negatives you enter without being excessive the better SD 2.1 preforms by the way!).

    IE: type cartoon if you want cartoon, realistic for real etc. call to it!! It has everything built in!! A few "realistic" keywords ? start with " masterpiece photo of... " and toss in "3d render, cartoon" into the negatives. =)

  • Sample gallery is random raw internet prompts on a fresh install - first try, no redo's, no backsies, sequentially numbered!, non cherry picked images. ( Fair is fair common! haha)

  • LOW Step count needed. Fantastic results in the 20-25 step range!

  • XYZ cat grid included to show 17,22,30 steps on all samplers (Standard CFG 7) "a cat lounging in the grass, basking in the morning sunshine" Note: some samplers do not work on (my) old gpu hence the few trash outputs. Apologies for those bits as it will probably work for you.)

-->>[ SFW/NSFW - ??? totally untested (to the level some people want). As it's a total merge, anything is possible so don't be mad if something slides in - just add a negative word prompt to compensate. See merging info below. ]
** The model "seems" and feels generally safe for work. Just..yeah! unknown! =)


WHAT IT LOVES AND HATES

It loves >??> Flowers certainly so far! (Bloody brilliant!) It also seems to understands a wider artistic range of broad subjects and prompts. only needing light negative prompting is a bonus as well. It also puts an interesting sort of "oil paint realistic edge" ?! as it's own artistic style to things.

It's good at >++> generally everything really ~ but more artistically than realistic from all the mixing. I randomized prompts from every site to make the gallery here and i find the results better in most cases when VS other general non purposely tuned model. (it seems to listen better)

It's bad at >--> For one it lost the face/hands of the realistic models being diluted and has trouble with them in general now. And Secondly, It takes a few tweaks here and there. Meaning you might need to bump the CFG or steps depending on your purpose. Bit of fiddling is required depending on your purpose. Think ..tuning a guitar! see next point.

-->> Not a bad point but really good to know: It's also a bit of a handful as larger models generally are, meaning sometimes you just need to run the same prompt a few times as it's got an eclectic mix of seeds deviating from the standard.


I found that you cannot rely on a single result at times as it just hit a "bad" seed for your scenario. It's a hugely packed model that has an enormous seed resource pool built in! Making it a handful... completing the irritating loop haha. See the mixing below)

Copyright >>> I personally don't give 2 hoots what you do. Know that this has every model from every human that made one in 768+ rez until now mixed in. If it had a yaml it's in here. So, like, you probably gotta kinda sorta maybe follow their rules as it was originally their models. =)

** To be clear of what is in this model merge. All working non biased overcooked models in 2.1, with working yaml file, in 768+ resolution, from aug '22 to feb '23 are merged in. (Approx 700GB of models total) - which is why the pruned versions cannot be lowered past the 5GB size. I'm sorry it's as small as I can crush it down without clipping data. The version 1 description below has the long tedious formula I use.


Post your comments and quibbles below.

Please enjoy responsibly!

BarQ!


> Hit the buymeacoffee link under my profile icon to help with the next R&D project!

> Visit my artstation link to view custom built offline AI creations as well!

modelVersions.name: 1.8L
modelVersions.description:
Version 1.8L (for loras!)

ALL the 2.1 based trained LORAS added in following the same blend schedule described before. (there is a difference between the SD1.5 versions fyi!)


What the model differences are:

1.8 = (the sloppy fun drunk) broad artistic vivid. Not scared to spill the wine while tipsy painting. Oh I made a Salvator Mundi? Cool.

Example: The flower rose prompts. Vivid & vibrant.

1.8L = Less drunk with a sharpened crayon. Dinosaurs? ya gotchya, I won't make them as gross (Thanks dino lora's!)


What the 1.8L LOSES > A chunk of it's upbeat sloppy creativity (flowers for instance are a darker shadier kind of cool.) It grew up a bit.

Examples: added samplers and examples to gallery for you to see yourself.

Does this beat any lora by itself? NO. A trained lora on only dinos for example will be better if you are only making dinos 24/7.


What this does is sharpen the pencils in the entire artist box. It makes it shape up a bit, mature - still a general model! But pulls it away from the original direction.

Think of those people who cook naturally then go to chef school ~ but that ruins their food a bit when they shape up to start cooking classically. You miss the older sloppier chef friend you had who didn't care about a four hundred dollar spice. haha ;)


Now you can decide what kind of crazy artistic wingman you want. =)


Notes: Future updates will continue down this path. Split + SplitLORA

******** HOW THE MERGING WAS DONE ********

Understanding Merging (and why it takes long)

Deck of cards merging analogy

In merging models you "shuffle them" together BUT keep the same number of cards. Take 2 decks of cards of different colors say Red and Black and shuffle your decks in real life with an attempt at 50/50 bias between them. BUT you also must end up with only 52 cards in your final deck after shuffling and you cannot look at the face values just the black/red colors.

The results with anything but a pristine deck is going to be a bias towards one color or the other. poker time. Flip your cards. Do you have more jacks? two's? aces? nobody knows until you look and see (try the model) only to play poker with all ones...nice...a mayo deck. pffff.

So after mixing you try models with the grid test xyz system across various prompts to expose it's weaknesses (you'll see in the added model screenshots)

This is what I did. Mix some cards > test the "new" 52 card decks > using xyz + discarding the junk output models (Rats I shuffled all 1,2,3's when I was trying to make a high royal flush deck or something) junk that one. check the other 1/2 mix which turned out better? neither? Remix.

It's a very tedious process!

*********

Base = Base SD2.1 768x768 model

base mix was 50/50 weighted sum Formula

Example:

Models A,B,C,D

Take A+B - find best mix = AB

Take C+D - find best mix = CD

Take base2.1 + AB - find best mix = bAB

Take Base2.1 + CD - find best mix = bCD

then merge bAB + bCD etc etc

merge all using same method in month one until left with a base 1.0

once complete, as you "lost cards" in the shuffle no matter what > take all the models in this batched mix and change to ABC "add difference" type card shuffle merging. This takes KitchenSink 1.0 base at a rate of 0.2 and re-feeds in "lost" cards back into the core breaking the 52 card deck limit.

Also making the model 28GB in size (yes gigs) when you are done re-adding all the missing bits. Loading it into the GPU memory is/was a nightmare heh.

[The incremental versions, 1.1, 1.2, 1.3 etc are the month(s) rollup of the models from SD's rough start in august '22 until now -> feb 23 2023 = 1.8 release for 8th month. Each month I would re-do the ABCD with only those models found in that period between themselves, then roll it into the previous kitchensink model. Incrementing upwards slowly having everything rolled into a ready to release model.][IE: all of this Marches models if any will be combined and merged into sink 1.8 to make 1.9 when the time comes. well feb 24th to march 23rd would be the next increment slice. haha]

items.name: Avalon TRUvision
items.description:
Version 3.1 is a hotfix, as the prune for v3 failed and was showing errors on peoples pictures.

(It is very dependant on negative prompts, so use the example images as a base.) The first image uses a light map as img2img so your results may very, but i thought it looked cool so i included it.

The model is better with a VAE. (vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned is fine or you can use your own.)

* For some reason (for V2) the pruned version isn't showing as the first download and the hashes have got screwy. Please use the dropdown menu to choose the smaller version if desired *

This model is a custom blend of various models, (see below), giving many options for generating a wide variety of images, including NSFW. Based on Stable Diffusion 1.5.

Primarily focused on capturing skin texture and the feel of photography, and Polaroids in general, but experiment with other things. (This model is not perfect).

Though there are is no specific KEYWORD to 'turn it on', if you use words in the prompt such as 'polaroid' , 'analog' , 'film grain', 'perfect eyes' and so forth at the start of the prompt, you should get the look you're after.

The example pictures do not have any face/eye correction or upscaling. 768 x 1024px is quite stable at producing images without 'mutation' if the prompt and neg prompt are good.

The model needs a VAE. (vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned is fine or you can use your own.)

Prompt example:

(polaroid), portrait, ((extreme realistic skin detail)), (20yo) (SUBJECT NAME or PERSON TYPE), ((holding a heart balloon)), lingerie, sassy, short black hair, sharp focus, detailed skin, detailed face, skin pores, skin imperfections, film grain, dynamic lighting,

Negative:

Child, jewellery, Plastic skin, Overexposed, (semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, digital art, anime, painting, manga), (deformed iris), distorted body, (deformed pupils), grit, man, distorted, (extra arms), long body, male, skin rash, deformed body, mutated hands, poorly drawn eyes, head crop, smooth skin , deformed hands, (deformed proportions) , long face, long neck, looking away, puffy nipples, watermark, logo, text,

or something like:

child, blur, old face, extra arms, big chin, (long neck!), ((more than one face)), imperfect eyes, glowing eyes, (head crop), pout, (abnormal body), double head, oversaturated, (head out of frame), too close, bad hands, distant, ugly, male, fake breasts, tiling, large nipples, extra heads, deformed, cgi, anime, painting, boring pose, plastic skin, extra limbs, big forehead, abnormal, long body, long limbs, overexposed, text, watermark, hairy body

A non-exhaustive lost of models merged (because I didn't take notes): deliberate, clarity, dreamlike-photoreal, realistic vision, protogen (+ additional ones in version notes).

Made for fun, not for money or notoriety. Those who train the models from scratch are the ones deserving of applause.

Have fun! Can't wait to see what you come up with...

items.name: zyd232's Chinese Girl LORA
items.description:
If you want to buy me a coffee, here's the link~

如果你想打赏我，这里是链接~

This LORA is created with more than 100 pictures of some cute Chinese girls. The resolution of these pics is 768*768. I recommend you use HI-RES to generate pics with this LoRA.

Theoretically, you can use it with any models based on SD 1.5. In order to get good results, I suggest you use this LoRA with those mixed models containing Asian female faces, such as shampooMix, ChilloutMix, RealDosMix, schoolmax 2.5d and so on.

　

For version 1.6 and 3.9:

In my tests, the perfect weight of this LoRA is around 0.4~0.7. If you find your other tags don't change the result, just try increasing the weight of your tags (1~1.5).

　

For version 4.0 and later:

You can use this LoRA with the weight of 1.0 or lower.

　

The negative prompt in example images has something wrong: the second half of the negative tags is duplicated with the prompt tags.

Just ignore it. (The problem is caused by an extension.)

　

You are welcome to share your pics generated with this LORA. But please keep those extremely NSFW ones to yourself.

　

-

　

这个LORA由一百多张可爱女生的照片炼成。分辨率为768*768。推荐使用高清修复（HI-RES）功能，以得到更多细节。

理论上，任何基于SD 1.5而炼成的模型都可以与这个LORA兼容。为了获得更好的结果，建议使用那些带有亚洲女性面孔的模型，比如 shampooMix、ChilloutMix、RealDosMix、schoolmax 2.5d 等等。

　

对于 version 1.6 及 3.9:

在我的测试中，此LORA的权重在0.4~0.7这个区间表现最好。如果你发现你的其他tag对结果产生的影响太小，可以尝试增加这些tag的权重（我的经验是增加到1~1.5）。

　

对于 version 4.0 以及更高版本：

这个 LoRA 的权重可以设为 1.0 或再低一些。

　

示例图片中的负面提示词有些问题：负面提示词后半部分的内容和提示词重复了。

请无视。（这个问题是由于我用的某个插件造成的。）

　

欢迎在评论区分享你用这个LORA生成的图片。但是请不要分享过于暴露的内容。

items.name: Catra LORA
items.description:
My first serious attempt at lora training. There's probably a lot that can be improved but I'm happy with the current results.

There doesn't seem to be as much loras/embeddings for characters from western animation so I decided to make some of my own.

NOTE: I use two negative embeddings in the generated images uploaded here, bad-artist and bad-hands-5. You can find them just by googling `bad-artist embedding`. Similar results are achievable with standard negative prompts.

I don't have a great understanding of lora training/concepts, but I trained a few different concepts in this lora. The two main concepts were images of catra in her military outfits with her red mask on, and the prompts had 'catra' only with other descriptors. Another concept was catra in her red dress suit, for those I used 'catra in a suit' prompt when training. It seems to trigger these correctly often enough. There's also a 'catra without mask' concept, although the mask disappears anyway if you start prompting hair/face details.

The Lora was trained on NAI, with clip skip set to 2. You'll get best results on NAI-like models, but I did get it to work on some realistic models.

For generation I mostly use DPM++ 2m karras or Euler a. Most of the photos I've created were pure txt2img with latent hires upscale. For a few with more complex poses, I used ControlNet with some catwoman comics images.

items.name: Ukiyo-e Style Enhancer
items.description:
Use:

As the name suggests this is meant to be an enhancer of style. You can use it in combination with other styles and artists to generate some interesting results or you can use it on its own but it's not a dedicated ukiyo-e model, only a textual inversion.

Enhancing:

Use it anywhere in the prompt, the further it is to the start the more influence it will have. Best used with other styles and artists.

On its own:

Start with "ukiyoestyle-1500 masterpiece"

Look at the sample images prompts to get an idea. I also included comparison of the two different versions with otherwise same settings.

Training:

This Textual Inversion was trained on 32 high quality ukiyo-e woodblock prints from Hokusai and Hiroshige.

The training images contained as many different elements as possible like people, landscape, animals, ships, buildings to make this embedding versatile.

Versions:

There are two versions included:

ukiyoestyle-1500 (regular) and ukiyoestyle-3000 (strong).

The "strong" version was trained more and has an interesing side effect:

Instead of making the style stronger it will make the images slightly more photorealistic if no specific style is prompted. Also it will occasionally bleed the trainings images content instead of applying the style. Which means it will tend to force asian faces and kimono. For example you will get a photorealistic woman wearing kimono instead of a woman wearing modern clothes in the style of ukiyo-e. See examples.

Suggestions:

Works well in combination with Ohara Koson Style Lora and specifically prompting ukiyo-e style.

items.name: Russian Doll Likeness
items.description:
This is my first Lora, please be nice and forgiving for any mishaps.

RussianDollV3

After being inspired by the Korean Doll Likeness by Kbr, I wanted to make one for more beautiful caucasian faces. Since I am deeply impressed by the Russian's high cheekbones, I decided to make a Lora to imitate this type of face. I know high cheekbones are not exclusive to Russia, but their models have a high percentage of this trait so I named it as such.

I trained this Lora with 28 images at the beginning, using a combination of (beautiful model, fit faces, and high cheekbones) in my prompts. No one or person was used as training data. From those 28 images, I made V1, which was unsatisfactory so I trained again with 100 steps, 8 epochs, and 6 batches to get V2. Using V2, I generated 24 more pics which I used to train for V3, the current model.

By no means is this model perfect, but it does get the high cheekbone that I find really attractive and sexy. There are two minor flaws: it is biased toward NSFW, and sometimes it generates a cleft chin. Just input them into the UC or add "SFW" and "sharp chin" in the prompt

Tips:

• The Lora works even better when there are (beautiful model and fit faces) in the prompt.

• I find the best result around 0.25~0.4. Don't go above 0.5 as it starts to get weird. The lora default is <lora:RussianDollV3:1>, remember to change it accordingly.

• This model works best in ChilloutMix. It also works decently well in 2.5D.

Disclaimer:

As the author, I regret to inform you that the LORA model is not intended for commercial use. This decision has been made in order to prevent any potential controversies or legal issues related to impersonation or defamation that may arise from the use of the model for commercial purposes. Furthermore, allowing commercial use of the model may have a negative impact on the development of the AI community. Therefore, I strongly advise against any commercial usage of the LORA model.

items.name: X-mix
items.description:
X-mix

X-mix 是一个用于生成二次元图片的融合模型。所有模型都没有添加vae，因此你需要自己设置一个。如果你想要生成与示例图风格一致的图片，请使用 NovelAI 原版 vae。如果你没有，可以用 OrangeMix 的 vae, 这两个vae 是一样的，只是名字不同。

llink: VAEs/orangemix.vae.pt · WarriorMama777/OrangeMixs at main (huggingface.co)

X-mix is a merging model used to generate anime images. This model needs a vae. You can freely choose the vae you like. If you want to achieve the effect in the example picture, please use NAI.vae.

link: VAEs/orangemix.vae.pt · WarriorMama777/OrangeMixs at main (huggingface.co)

V2.0

V2.0 并不比 V1.0 表现更优秀（其实我本人更喜欢用 V1.0），但风格发生了变化。除此之外，还有以下变化：

  • 好消息：由于 V1.0 不够涩，我特意让 V2.0 比 V1.0 更涩（喜）。坏消息：涩过头了（喜）（悲），有时候不想涩涩都不行（好像也不是什么缺点）。

  • 似乎变得难用了

The performance of V2.0 is not better than that of V1.0, but the generated images now exhibit a different artistic style.

V2.0 offers better support for nsfw than V1.0, but the drawback is that even when you do not intend to generate an nsfw image, there is still a possibility of generating one.

In my opinion, V2.0 is not as user-friendly as V1.0, and it appears to be more challenging to generate an excellent image.

V1.0

忘了怎么融了，只知道用了一堆模型。这个模型支持nsfw，但是效果不是很好，因为我在融合模型的时候并没有考虑涩涩。

我个人感觉这个模型挺好用的，不用费很大劲去写 tag 都能出一张还不错的图片，很适合我这种懒人。

I have forgotten the recipe for X-mix-V1.0, as too many models were used for merging. This model supports nsfw, but the effect may not be very good.

You can generate a good image using this model without having to put in a lot of effort to write prompts.

More

  • 我没办法对每个模型进行充分的测试，因为我的显卡就是依托答辩。因此欢迎你们在评论发图，并反馈你们遇到的问题，这对我很有帮助。

  • 更多信息在 huggingface 上，我通常会先把新模型上传到 huggingface 再写文档。不过 huggingface 上面全是我的垃圾英语，没有中文，希望这没有给你们带来困扰。les-chien/X-mix · Hugging Face

  • I can't perform comprehensive tests on every model because I get a shit GPU. So, please feel free to share your images and provide feedback on any issues you encounter in the comments section. This is very helpful to me.

  • More information on: les-chien/X-mix · Hugging Face

items.name: zPose Catwalk Styles 1 (pose helper)
items.description:
Carefully curated selection of 30 workable poses with preview images and prompts. Follow me to make sure you see new poses when I post them. Things move fast on this site, it's easy to miss.

Download the zip file. Inside are 30 (total) .png files used for poses and 30 json files so you have more control. Requires the ControlNet extension for Automatic1111. If you don't know what those 2 things are, check out some youtube tutorials on setting them up.

I've saved you some time and meticulously prepared 30 different catwalk fashion model stance poses that the Stable Diffusion models can handle pretty well. Some easier than others. Some diffusion models will have better results than others. The sample images here were generated using the legendary A to Zovya RPG Artist's Tools model.

How to use:

Download the zip file. Inside are the poses that you will instruct controlnet to use instead of generating one from an existing image. Craft your prompt as you usually would. Let the model know with prompts, this is a (standing / walking / posing) stance pose to help it along. In the controlnet settings, choose "none" for the preprocessor and "openpose" for the model. Adjust weight depending on how difficult the model wants to be. The pose images provided are 512x768 aspect ratio of 2:3. You can crop or add to the existing images with your favorite program to customize your composition.

Do you have requests? I've been putting in many more hours lately with this. That's my problem, not yours. But if you'd like to tip me, buy me a beer. Beer encourages me to ignore work and make AI models instead. Tip and make a request. I'll give it a shot if I can. Here at Ko-Fi

A gacha splash style lora. Make sure you start with the following template and add your background prompts.

[(white background:1.5)::5], isometric OR hexagon , 1 girl, mid shot, full body, <add your background prompts here>

Suggested resolution: 640X640 with hires fix. You may modify your prompt and resolution after successfully getting the effect.

I trained two different versions with different learning rate and scheduler.

Gacha Splash Fantasy fits more in abstract backgrounds.

Gacha Splash is intentionally trained to be slightly overfit. It fits greatly for architectures.

See compares from sample images

Notes:

1. If your characters are always wearing jackets/half off jackets, try adding "off shoulder" in negative prompt. You may further add "jackets"/ "bare shoulders" if the issue persists.

2. Similar as the jacket issue, if you find any elements that are always being generated, try adding them into negative prompt first. The training dataset is well tagged. Therefore AI should be able to remove these elements.

Prompts like hexagon and isometric help to shape the gacha splash effect. There are some alternative choices.

items.description:
The third take on this is probably the last release until we get new tech to make better models. I'm including multiple versions so make sure you read the release notes!

V3 should work on most every 1.5 model. The sweet spot seems to be around 0.7-0.9 for most models, but you can do between 0.3-1.4 usually depending on desired effect.

You may want to add some or all of the keywords to the prompt depending on which outfit you are trying to get her to wear.

modelVersions.name: v3-128-32
modelVersions.description: 128 dimension model shrunk to 32. More consistent but less flexible. Generally trends more painterly/digital art/illustration than the native 32 dim model.

modelVersions.name: V3-32
modelVersions.description: 32 dimension model. Trained on the same dataset but different seed from the 128. Likes to do 2.5/3d style usually when not prompted otherwise. Can be less stable with respect to anatomy than the 128.

modelVersions.name: V3-32-merge
modelVersions.description: This is the merge of the 128-32 and 32 dimension models. It gives different results than either. More consistent artstyle but tends to add mutations more often than either of the parent models.

modelVersions.name: v3-128-4
modelVersions.description: 128 dimension shrunk to 4. Just as rigid as the other 4 dim models but tends towards more animated or digital art styling than the 32.

modelVersions.name: v3-32-4
modelVersions.description: 32 dimension model shrunk to 4 dimensions. More consistent but less flexible. Likes to do more 2.5/3d styles without artists specified, just like the full 32 dim.

modelVersions.name: V3-4-merge
modelVersions.description: This is the merge of the 128-4 and 32-4 dimension models. It gives different results than either and is consistent but tends to just give you red haired elves.

modelVersions.name: v2
modelVersions.description: Much more usable and requires few negative prompts. Need more positive prompts now if you want her armor and gear to spawn in. Except that damn circlet.

可以通过范例图片查看每件衣服的生成咒语。实例内可能有些图片的关键词和版本号可能与V0.2不匹配，不过作为起步点应当是足够了:)

items.name: Shimakaze (kancolle) - Character
items.description:
UPDATE: removed noise offset, slightly less training, better for combining with multiple other LoRAs

Finally, after much trial and error, I believe this LoRA came out really well. But you be the judge: let me know what you think and post your own generated images. See features, how to use and examples below.

New features:

  • easy to make good gens on anime models like AOM2 (click "view more" in the gallery to see non cherry-picked batches)

  • compatible with other LoRAs, to fit your style, pose and even use it as an outfit/cosplay for other characters, since you can change hair color

  • works with various models, including anime, 2.5D and realistic (some realistic models may require more tweaking the prompt, weight and CFG to get the best results; see my examples)

How to use:

  • Works with weight 0.6-1.0 and CFG 5-8 , depending on the model (e.g. higher weight and CFG for realistic models)

  • Main trigger word: shimakaze

  • The main trigger word will generally provide the outfit, but these trigger words can be used to emphasize the character/outfit: blonde hair, striped thighhighs, microskirt, elbow gloves, sailor collar, anchor hair ornament, highleg panties, black panties

  • Other keywords associated with the character and context: robot, turret, lifebuoy

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

Stable Diffusion also has a tendency to try and render Harry into pictures, add 'prince harry' to your negative prompt to prevent this.

items.name: Image soften LORA (AOM)
items.description:
This model can be used to soften AbyssOrangeMix's sharp edges style while keeping the good composition qualities of the checkpoint.

This lora will may modify the composition a little bit; sometimes it is desirable and the results are interesting, while sometimes it is not. In that case, I recommend using ControlNet with the image you are trying to soften.

Experiment with the lora weight, even at 1+ it doesn't cook as much as one would think.


Works well with abyssOrangeMix 2 and 3, may work with other models in the family (untested).

Enjoy!
